     3→  "classification": "Strong",
     4→  "implication": "G6PD deficiency impairs NADPH regeneration in red blood cells. Rasburicase catalyzes the oxidation of uric acid to allantoin, producing hydrogen peroxide (H2O2) as a byproduct. In G6PD-deficient individuals, the lack of sufficient NADPH prevents adequate reduction of glutathione, leaving red blood cells unable to neutralize H2O2-mediated oxidative stress. This results in severe, potentially life-threatening hemolytic anemia. The FDA label carries a black box warning for hemolytic anemia and methemoglobinemia in G6PD-deficient patients."
